64","1330":"1330","about 1330":"about 1330","Midlothian, Scotland":"Midlothian, Scotland, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Scotland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Napier","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English and Scottish: occupational name from Old French <i>napier</i>, <i>nappier</i>, <i>nap(p)er(er)</i> ‘one who looks after the napery or table-linen’, a derivative of Old French <i>nappe</i> ‘table-cloth, napkin’. In Middle English, <i>Napier</i> and <i>Nap(p)er</i> might also have denoted a maker of table cloths, though this sense has not been recorded.","English: alternatively an occupational name from <i>Nap(p)er</i> from an unrecorded Middle English word for one who makes <i>naps</i>, i.e. drinking cups or chalices (Middle English <i>nap</i>, Old English <i>hnæp</i>). <i>Napper</i> could also be a nickname from Middle English <i>nappere</i> ‘one who sleeps or naps’, though this is the least likely of the alternatives.","American shortened form of Polish   Napierala   or a similar name."],"variants":[{"name":"Napper","meanings":["English: variant of   Napier  .","Altered form of English or German   Knapper   or of German   Nepper  ."]},{"name":"Nappier","meanings":["English: variant of   Napier  . This surname is now rare in Britain."]},{"name":"Napierala","meanings":["Polish (<b>Napierała</b>): nickname for an insistent person,from a derivative of <i>napierać</i> ‘advance, press, urge’."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William Napier was born about 1330, in Scotland as the son of John Napier. He had at least 1 son with Mrs William Napier. He died after 1401."},"et":{"about 1330–after 1401":"umbes 1330–pärast 1401","1330–1401":"1330–1401","1335–Female":"1335–Surnud","1364–1454":"1364–1454","–Male":"Surnud","after 1401":"pärast 1401","1335":"1335","1401":"1401","1454":"1454","1364":"1364","1330":"1330","about 1330":"umbes 1330","Midlothian, Scotland":"Midlothian, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Scotland"},"fi":{"about 1330–after 1401":"noin 1330–1401 jälkeen","1330–1401":"1330–1401","1335–Female":"1335–Kuollut","1364–1454":"1364–1454","–Male":"Kuollut","after 1401":"1401 jälkeen","1335":"1335","1401":"1401","1454":"1454","1364":"1364","1330":"1330","about 1330":"noin 1330","Midlothian, Scotland":"Midlothian, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Scotland":"Scotland"},"fr":{"about 1330–after 1401":"environ 1330–après 1401","1330–1401":"1330–1401","1335–Female":"1335–Décédée","1364–1454":"1364–1454","–Male":"Décédé","after 1401":"après 1401","1335":"1335","1401":"1401","1454":"1454","1364":"1364","1330":"1330","about 1330":"environ 1330","Midlothian, Scotland":"Midlothian, Écosse, Royaume-Uni","Scotland":"Écosse","lifeSummary":"William Napier est né environ 1330, à Écosse, fils de John Napier. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Mrs William Napier. Il est décédé après 1401."},"de":{"about 1330–after 1401":"um 1330–nach 1401","1330–1401":"1330–1401","1335–Female":"1335–Verstorben","1364–1454":"1364–1454","–Male":"Verstorben","after 1401":"nach 1401","1335":"1335","1401":"1401","1454":"1454","1364":"1364","1330":"1330","about 1330":"um 1330","Midlothian, Scotland":"Midlothian, Schottland, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Sc